translated: Camp, Sven Air, naval medical doctor of the 1st degree, licensed physician, from Karlskrona, born on July 20th, 1911 in the Raus parish of Hälsingborg to the district governor Arvid C. and Edel Melchior. He married Gunn Bendrup in 1942, and they had three children: Peder, born in 1943, Mette in 1944, and Willie in 1945. Sven passed his high school exams in Malmö in 1929, became a medical candidate in Lund in 1935, and received his medical license there in 1941. He was a stand-in doctor at hospitals in Trelleborg and Gällivare, naval medical fellow of the state in 1940, naval medical fellow in Mlk (presumably Malmen Airbase) in 1941, naval medical doctor of the 2nd degree in Mlk in 1942, the 1st degree from 1944, and a medical doctor of the navy's sailor school in Karlskrona since 1944.
